---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: International comparison
description: How UK government debt compares with other major economies, using a consistent international measure.
---
{% from "components/macros.njk" import caveatBox, dataFreshnessBadge %}

<div class="page-intro prose">
  <h1>International comparison</h1>
  <p class="lede">How the UK sits against other major economies, on a measure chosen to be comparable across countries.</p>
</div>

{{ caveatBox(internationalComparisons.caveat, "Comparing like with like") }}

<section aria-labelledby="table-heading">
  <h2 id="table-heading">{{ internationalComparisons.measure }}, {{ internationalComparisons.year }}</h2>
  <div class="table-scroll" tabindex="0" role="region" aria-label="International debt comparison table">
    <table class="data-table">
      <caption>Sorted from highest to lowest debt-to-GDP. Debt is the 2025 estimate; deficit and growth are 2024 outturn.</caption>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Country</th>
          <th scope="col" class="num">Debt %GDP</th>
          <th scope="col" class="num">Deficit %GDP</th>
          <th scope="col" class="num">Growth %</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {%- for c in internationalComparisons.countries | sort(true, false, "debtToGdp") %}
        <tr{% if c.id == "uk" %} class="is-highlight"{% endif %}>
          <th scope="row">{{ c.name }}{% if c.id == "uk" %} <span class="tag">UK</span>{% endif %}</th>
          <td class="num">{{ c.debtToGdp }}</td>
          <td class="num">{{ c.deficitToGdp }}</td>
          <td class="num">{{ c.gdpGrowth }}</td>
        </tr>
        {%- endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<p class="source-note">
  Debt figures: <a href="{{ internationalComparisons.source_url }}" rel="noopener">{{ internationalComparisons.source_name }}</a>, {{ internationalComparisons.year }}.
  Retrieved {{ internationalComparisons.retrieved_date | readableDate }}.
  {{ dataFreshnessBadge(internationalComparisons.confidence_level, "") }}
</p>

<section class="prose" aria-labelledby="note-heading">
  <h2 id="note-heading">Why the UK number here differs from the headline</h2>
  <p>This table uses <strong>general government gross debt</strong>, the most consistent measure across countries. The UK's own headline measure (public sector net debt, around 95% of GDP) is lower because it subtracts liquid assets and is defined slightly differently. Comparing countries fairly means using the same definition for all of them, even if it is not the one a country usually quotes at home.</p>
</section>
